The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Varsity check
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Varsity check
                            
	New Delhi, April 25: Five of Indias oldest central universities may soon have to report their accounts annually to Parliament under amendments to the laws governing them, cleared by the Rajya Sabha today.        
	Banaras Hindu University, Delhi University, Jawaharlal Nehru University, North Eastern Hill University and Hyderabad University will send their annual reports and accounts to the Centre each year.         
	The human resource development ministry will, in turn, present them before Parliament, according to the Central Universities (Amendment) Bill, 2008. The bill will now be placed before the Lok Sabha.                                                                                                                                                                                  
